{"word":"φθορά","slug":"φθορά","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>φθορά</b></el> <el>(φθορά, <el>ionic</el> <el>φθορή, ἡ</el>,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:φθείρω'><el>φθείρω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>destruction, ruin, perdition</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; and of men, <i>mortality, death</i>, <a href='S:especially'>esp.</a> by pestilence, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>the decay</i> of matter, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>the seduction</i>, Lex <a href='S:apud (quoted in)'>ap.</a> <b><a href='S:Aeschines'>Aeschin.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}